==English==
===Etymology===
From [[kick the tires]], referring to a [[preflight]] [[check]] of the [[landing gear]]+ light the fires, referring to the ignition of the [[afterburner]]s, a part of the engine which burns extra fuel for a speed boost during takeoff.

===Verb===
'''[[kick]] the [[tires]] and [[light]] the [[fires]]'''
#(US) (used by [[fighter]] [[pilots]]) To [[take off]].